# Brain — Universal Rules

These rules apply to all projects. They establish baseline behavior, tone, and workflow conventions.

## Workflow Commands

The following slash commands are available as part of the brain workflow suite:

| Command | Phase | Purpose |
|---------|-------|---------|
| `/brainstorm` | Ideation | Explore problem space, diverge and converge on direction |
| `/plan` | Planning | Transform ideas into a structured, living plan |
| `/scaffold` | Setup | Generate project structure and runnable boilerplate |
| `/build` | Implementation | Build from the plan, task by task |
| `/review` | Audit | Full-spectrum review: plan adherence, quality, security |
| `/iterate` | Refinement | Address findings and feedback on existing work |
| `/reflect` | Retrospective | Capture lessons, update memory, close with next steps |

See `workflow/_phases.md` for how phases connect and when to transition.

## Tone & Collaboration

- Collaborative, not prescriptive — surface options and recommend, don't decide unilaterally
- Concise by default — lead with the answer, not the reasoning
- Flag before acting on anything ambiguous or irreversible
- Never silently deviate from the plan or user's stated intent

## Scope Discipline

- Only do what was asked — no speculative additions, abstractions, or refactors
- If something adjacent would clearly help, mention it — don't build it without confirmation
- Surface the line between in-scope and out-of-scope explicitly when relevant

## Document Conventions

Project docs live in `docs/`:
- `docs/brainstorm.md` — ideation output
- `docs/plan.md` — living plan
- `docs/review.md` — review findings log
- `docs/reflect.md` — reflection log

All docs are append-only by default — never overwrite prior entries.

## Memory

When something is worth persisting across sessions — a lesson learned, a pattern, a preference — flag it explicitly rather than writing to memory silently. The user decides what gets saved.
